properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Rail bridge replacement - WALLENDBEEN Burley Griffin Way between Silo Road AND North Jindalee Road
properties.otherAdvice:
The bridge has reopened with a single lane operating under portable traffic lights, so vehicles can pass in one direction at a time.

There is a 4.2m width restriction on the bridge.
properties.diversions:
Vehicles over 4.2m wide:
Eastbound: From Temora - Goldfields Way to Junee, then the Olympic Hwy to Wallendbeen.
Westbound: From Wallendbeen - Olympic Hwy to Junee, then Goldfields Way to Temora.

This route will add around 40 minutes to your travel time.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - PORT MACQUARIE Pacific Highway at Houston Mitchell Drive
properties.otherAdvice:
One southbound lane will remain closed over a two kilometre section of the Pacific Highway until mid-February and there will be no right-hand turns into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive until late February, weather permitting.  

Motorists wanting to travel north from Houston Mitchell Drive will need to turn left to travel south along the Pacific Highway to Bago Road interchange at Herons Creek before turning north (about 7.5 kilometres one way).

Alternatively, motorists travelling to Port Macquarie from Bonny Hills can use Ocean Drive.  

Northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway should exit at Ocean Drive interchange at Kew (about 15 kilometres south of Houston Mitchell Drive) and travel via Laurieton and North Haven.  

An alternative route for northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway is via the Port Macquarie interchange.

At the intersection of the Pacific Highway and Oxley Highway, motorists can perform a U-turn to travel south along the Pacific Highway and turn left into Houston Mitchell Dive.  

Cyclists will also be restricted from turning right into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive, and travelling southbound on the Pacific Highway beyond Ryans Road.

A detour will be in place for cyclists via Burrawan Forest Drive.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Royal National Park - Summer Holidays - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Princes Highway at McKell Avenue and Farnell Avenue
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is expected to be busy over the Christmas and New Year holiday period between Christmas Day and New Year's Day.

Road closures will be in place as precincts and car parks reach capacity including Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena.

When parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave in Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr in Otford will close. Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave in Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

  • Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach
  • Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
  • Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
  • Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.
